# Who Talks to Whom

A data visualization exploring collaboration patterns across design teams during Q2 2026. Built as a single-page app with vanilla HTML, CSS, and JavaScript (D3.js).

## What It Shows

Three interactive views of how 57 people across 5 teams connect:

1. **Network Graph** — Force-directed graph where lines connect people who collaborated. Thicker lines = more days working together. Hover to highlight individual connections; hover team names in the legend to filter.

2. **Team Heatmap** — Shows total collaboration days between each pair of teams. Quickly surfaces which teams are tightly linked and which rarely interact.

3. **Collaboration Profile** — Beeswarm chart grouping people by team. Height shows what % of their work crosses team boundaries. Bigger circles = more total collaboration days.

Each view includes an analysis panel with plain-language insights and suggestions.

## Running Locally

Open `index.html` in any modern browser. No build step, no server required.

```
# Or use a local server if you prefer:
npx serve .
```

## Files

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `index.html` | App shell — header, tabs, chart containers, footer |
| `styles.css` | All styling (CSS custom properties, grid layout) |
| `app.js` | Data, D3 visualizations, analysis logic |
| `BRIEF.md` | Original project brief and design intent |

## Data

All data is synthetic and embedded in `app.js`. It models:
- 57 people across 5 teams (Design, Engineering, Product, Research, Ops)
- ~120 collaboration edges with weights representing "days connected" over 65 working days
- No real names or actual communication content

## Dependencies

- [D3.js v7](https://d3js.org/) — loaded via CDN, no install needed

## Browser Support

Any modern browser (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge). No IE support.